&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://click.appcast.io/greenhouse-te8/a31.png?ent=34&amp;amp;e=22630&amp;amp;t=1701374353806&quot; width=&quot;1px&quot;&gt; &lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://track.jobadx.com/v1/i.gif?utm_pixel=224e990b-8ff4-4287-8d5d-2ff09647f181&amp;amp;utm_ptz=EST&amp;amp;utm_rqt=track&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At DoorDash, our mission is to empower local economies – and the Inside Sales Account Executive team lives that mission every day. We partner directly with local restaurant owners and operators, helping them reach new customers and build a real revenue stream through on-demand delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We invest in our people the same way we invest in our merchants. That means hands-on coaching, clear performance feedback, and a real career path – into senior sales, field sales, strategic sales, or leadership. If you want to grow in sales, this is the team to join.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an &lt;strong&gt;Account Executive (AE)&lt;/strong&gt; on our Inside Sales team, you will own the full sales cycle from prospecting to close. This is a high-volume, transactional role with deal cycles that close within a few days to a week. Most of your day is outbound calls — you’ll be running a high volume of conversations simultaneously, so comfort with fast-paced outreach and short deal cycles is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our most successful AEs are consistent and self-motivated. They build healthy pipelines, follow up consistently, and treat every conversation as an opportunity to move the deal forward. You’ll have a manager invested in your growth and a team around you, but you’ll also have real ownership over your results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is flexible, with some time in office and some time remote. You will need the ability to travel as needed for in-person collaboration through training, offsites, team-building events, and other business-related necessities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll be doing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prospect and close new restaurant partners, managing the full sales cycle from first outreach to signed deal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate pipeline through a mix of assigned leads and self-sourced outreach — cold calls, emails, and creative prospecting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run high-volume discovery calls and move multiple deals forward simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with restaurant owners and operators from first contact through close&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep CRM data accurate, maintain forecast discipline, and manage your pipeline with operational rigor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage AI tools that make you sharper, faster, and more effective in your role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1+ years of outbound or high-volume sales&lt;/strong&gt; experience, ideally in a closing role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort running a high volume of conversations and short deal cycles without losing momentum&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An understanding of how daily activity translates into pipeline and revenue — and you hold yourself to that standard&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong objection handling skills and confidence navigating challenging sales conversations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of hitting targets and holding yourself accountable to your numbers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Openness to coaching — you hear feedback, apply it, and look for ways to keep improving&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Curiosity about AI tools and how to use them to work more effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus if you have experience in restauran

